==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Slay
<hw>Slay</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos>
<conjf>Slew</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. p.</pos> <conjf>Slain</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Slaying</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>slan</ets>,
<ets>sl<?/n</ets>, <ets>sleen</ets>, <ets>slee</ets>, AS.
<ets>sle⟦aacute⟧n</ets> to strike, beat, slay; akin to OFries.
<ets>sl⟦amac⟧</ets>, D. <ets>slaan</ets>, OS. & OHG. <ets>slahan</ets>,
G. <ets>schlagen</ets>, Icel. <ets>sl⟦amac⟧</ets>, Dan.
<ets>slaae</ets>, Sw. <ets>sl<?/</ets>, Goth. <ets>slahan</ets>; perhaps
akin to L. <ets>lacerare</ets> to tear to pieces, Gr. <?/<?/<?/<?/, E.
<ets>lacerate</ets>. Cf. <er>Slaughter</er>, <er>Sledge</er> a hammer,
<er>Sley</er>.]</ety> <def>To put to death with a weapon, or by
violence; hence, to kill; to put an end to; to destroy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With this sword then will I <qex>slay</qex> you both.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will <qex>slay</qex> the last of them with the sword.</q>
<rj><qau>Amos ix. 1.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I'll <qex>slay</qex> more gazers than the basilisk.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To kill; murder; slaughter; butcher.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slayer</ent>⟦br⟧
